name: Yozelinm/AD340-MyFirstAndroidApp
description: Create a new project in Android Studio, with a name that will be appropriate as you extend the application throughout this course.  Select a minimum API level that works for at least 80% of Android devices. For now, it's ok to support just phones in portrait mode.  Your application should have a single main activity that displays your info on app launch.   Be sure to review your application in an Android virtual device (simulator) before committing to git.  Submit your github.com repository link in Canvas. Your repository should contain all Android files needed to build and run the application on an Android device without errors.
